track_notes:
Park in space on south (left side) of road at disused mine at SH 683 336. Do not drive any further as there are no parking places closer to the end of the road at the farm.
Walk west along the road until just before the farm entrance, take the obvious rough track leaving the road to the north.  Follow this through a couple of gates until it ends at SH 664 344. Continue on the same line for another 100m or so until a grassy break in the rocks above becomes apparent.  There is a small indistinct path which now climbs directly up the slope through the wall at SH 661 344.  Continue up the slope until you reach the summit.  Cairn and trig point. Plenty of room for antennas.  Nice views to the north across the estuary.

Parking at SH629342 (£2 charge donated to air ambulance). Follow mine track and branch left at SH63733424. When Bryn Cader Faner comes into view follow obvious track to the stone circle. Head east crossing valley and pick up quad bike track. Climb up to Llyn Dywarchen (small manganese mine here). Skirt edge to boulder field to below cliffs. Follow to the right and loop up behind, which takes you to the summit.
track_title: From west via Bryn Cader Faner

track_notes: Parking at SH629342 (£2 charge donated to air ambulance). Simply follow the mine track, keeping right at SH63733424. At SH651347 branch right to workings of Llyn Dywarchen mine. Continue south east along obvious mine track, to Llyn Du Bach mine. Loop anti-clockwise around the hill. At the end of the track keep going across rock slabs and boggy area to pick up a track heading NNE towards the summit.
